1175
01:31:13.579 --> 01:31:16.582
It states that the University
of California hands over


1176
01:31:16.707 --> 01:31:20.127
a plutonium core of a nuclear device
to the United States Army.


1177
01:31:20.252 --> 01:31:25.549
Put more simply,
it's a bill for two billion dollars.


1178
01:31:27.009 --> 01:31:30.763
Now, let me show you
what else your money's bought.


1179
01:31:31.931 --> 01:31:34.892
The initiator.

1180
01:31:36.936 --> 01:31:40.189
And the other half.

1181
01:31:40.773 --> 01:31:45.403
Now, all we got to do
is throw them together and...


1182
01:31:47.822 --> 01:31:51.659
Well, let's begin
final assembly.


1183
01:31:55.454 --> 01:31:58.749
OK, Mr. Merriman.

1184
01:32:10.094 --> 01:32:13.264
Well, you're quiet.

1185
01:32:14.974 --> 01:32:18.352
It's coming close, what you're
working towards, isn't it?


1186
01:32:18.477 --> 01:32:20.688
Yeah.

1187
01:32:20.813 --> 01:32:24.525
I can feel it pressing down
on everybody.


1188
01:32:24.650 --> 01:32:28.321
There's something going on here.

1189
01:32:29.196 --> 01:32:32.908
It's got everybody mesmerized,
doesn't it?


1190
01:32:33.034 --> 01:32:35.119
Yeah.

1191
01:32:35.244 --> 01:32:38.998
There's a regular run
on sleeping pills and aspirin.


1192
01:32:39.123 --> 01:32:43.502
And it's not just the work,
it's something else.


1193
01:32:46.005 --> 01:32:50.301
- Look, I know you can't talk about it.
- I can't.


1194
01:32:50.426 --> 01:32:53.596
Well, then talk to Dr. Oppenheimer.

1195
01:32:53.721 --> 01:32:57.933
I mean, if anyone has,
he'll have thought it through, right?


1196
01:32:58.392 --> 01:33:00.895
OK.

1197
01:33:06.400 --> 01:33:09.445
Touch me.

1198
01:33:24.710 --> 01:33:26.921
Naked.

1199
01:33:27.046 --> 01:33:30.424
Isn't that a beautiful word?

1200
01:33:32.468 --> 01:33:35.012
Tonight.

1201
01:33:35.137 --> 01:33:38.474
I want to make love.

1202
01:33:40.643 --> 01:33:43.020
And I want a future.

1203
01:33:43.145 --> 01:33:45.815
That's what I really want...

1204
01:33:45.940 --> 01:33:48.275
for you and me.

1205
01:33:48.401 --> 01:33:51.570
So do I.

1206
01:33:53.197 --> 01:33:58.119
- Oh, for chrissake, George.
- This pitting, must be the mold.


1207
01:33:58.244 --> 01:34:00.871
I'm not an explosives expert,
but I've been called


1208
01:34:00.997 --> 01:34:03.207
to look at something
that's unacceptable.


1209
01:34:03.332 --> 01:34:04.792
We must use hand lathings.

1210
01:34:04.917 --> 01:34:07.294
You should have used hand
lathings before.


1211
01:34:07.420 --> 01:34:10.673
- Hand lathings, you know what it is?
- Yes.


1212
01:34:10.798 --> 01:34:14.969
- Michael, what are you doing here?
- Chicago, Leo Szilard.


1213
01:34:15.094 --> 01:34:17.805
I read it on the train.

1214
01:34:17.930 --> 01:34:22.560
- Well, what do you think about it?
- It unnerved me.


1215
01:34:23.269 --> 01:34:25.730
Are we gonna discuss this ever?

1216
01:34:25.855 --> 01:34:28.691
Amongst ourselves?

1217
01:34:28.816 --> 01:34:32.903
- Are we going on?
- I don't see anyone stopping.


1218
01:34:33.029 --> 01:34:36.324
Now, look, we've been asked
to solve a technical problem,


1219
01:34:36.449 --> 01:34:40.077
to build this device.
We're not responsible for its use.


1220
01:34:40.202 --> 01:34:43.581
Oppie, it's for you.

1221
01:34:43.706 --> 01:34:47.543
Peter's got revised figures.

1222
01:34:53.424 --> 01:34:57.345
Look, let me keep this paper.

1223
01:34:57.470 --> 01:35:01.474
We're expecting the initiator.
We need your lab results, all right?


1224
01:35:01.599 --> 01:35:03.309
All right?

1225
01:35:03.434 --> 01:35:06.228
All right.

1226
01:35:25.373 --> 01:35:27.166
Everybody ready?

1227
01:35:27.291 --> 01:35:29.960
- Meter's ready.
- Here we go.


1228
01:35:49.271 --> 01:35:52.191
Twenty-one.

1229
01:35:58.155 --> 01:36:00.908
Twenty-nine.

1230
01:36:09.917 --> 01:36:12.962
Thirty-one.

1231
01:36:14.588 --> 01:36:17.216
Thirty-eight.

1232
01:36:17.508 --> 01:36:22.430
Got it? Forty.
Everybody back, right now.


1233
01:36:27.893 --> 01:36:30.312
Behind the wall.

1234
01:36:41.115 --> 01:36:43.617
Turn it off!

1235
01:36:50.666 --> 01:36:53.461
Nobody move! Don't anybody move!

1236
01:36:56.547 --> 01:36:59.008
Damn it!

1237
01:36:59.133 --> 01:37:01.218
Take off everything metal.
Drop it.


1238
01:37:01.344 --> 01:37:05.222
Mark the positions
you're standing in and get out.


1239
01:37:08.142 --> 01:37:09.685
The incident never happened.

1240
01:37:09.810 --> 01:37:13.648
If anyone should ask,
it did not happen.


1241
01:37:34.168 --> 01:37:37.338
Everybody should make it.

1242
01:37:38.422 --> 01:37:41.050
Except me.

1243
01:37:41.175 --> 01:37:43.969
I'm dead.

1244
01:38:04.949 --> 01:38:07.785
Doctor! Doctor!
I've been looking all over for you.


1245
01:38:07.910 --> 01:38:10.538
We've got a problem.

1246
01:38:10.663 --> 01:38:11.956
- Bad allergy.
- When?


1247
01:38:12.081 --> 01:38:14.542
- An hour ago. They're bringing him in.
- Who?


1248
01:38:14.667 --> 01:38:16.002
Mr. Merriman.

1249
01:38:16.127 --> 01:38:17.878
- Michael?
- Yes, sir.


1250
01:38:18.004 --> 01:38:20.006
Oh, shit.

1251
01:38:20.131 --> 01:38:22.383
Let's go.

1252
01:38:22.508 --> 01:38:26.220
- Come on, let's go!
- Yes, sir.


1253
01:38:32.351 --> 01:38:34.979
This one won't do.

1254
01:38:37.106 --> 01:38:40.901
- In here. This one's good.
- Take it easy. All right, all right.


1255
01:38:41.027 --> 01:38:45.114
- Michael, what's the matter?
- Nothing, everything's fine.


1256
01:38:45.239 --> 01:38:48.242
- Doctor, how much did he get?
- More than 1,000 rads.


1257
01:38:48.367 --> 01:38:50.202
- Goddamn it.
- What's happening?


1258
01:38:50.328 --> 01:38:54.707
Sweetheart, it's under control.
Everything's under control, OK?


1259
01:38:54.915 --> 01:38:57.752
- Steven, what's going on?
- You should not be here.


1260
01:38:57.877 --> 01:38:59.754
Excuse me, there's no patient here.

1261
01:38:59.879 --> 01:39:02.798
No one's to hear about this.
Not Oppenheimer. Nobody.


1262
01:39:02.923 --> 01:39:06.427
- OK?
- Goddamn it, what happened here?


1263
01:39:06.552 --> 01:39:08.846
I want this ward sealed off.
Come with me.


1264
01:39:08.971 --> 01:39:12.558
I want military doctors in here.

1265
01:39:21.692 --> 01:39:24.570
Get the hell out of here!

1266
01:39:28.282 --> 01:39:30.660
It's the detonation circuits.

1267
01:39:32.036 --> 01:39:36.040
I don't know.
I would like another 24 hours.


1268
01:39:36.165 --> 01:39:39.210
I think so, but I can't be certain.

1269
01:39:39.335 --> 01:39:45.549
I said one more day.
I need one more day.


1270
01:39:45.925 --> 01:39:51.389
No, no, Merriman brought me
a copy from Chicago.


1271
01:39:51.514 --> 01:39:53.557
Some of the physicists
have signed it.


1272
01:39:53.683 --> 01:39:57.603
Pinko fruitcakes. Get that thing
to work, I'm gonna drop it on Chicago.


1273
01:39:57.728 --> 01:40:00.314
I swear I will.

1274
01:40:00.439 --> 01:40:06.362
Yes, I hear you. You hear me?
Finish the damn thing. That's an order.


1275
01:40:07.363 --> 01:40:11.033
Well, I got other business.

1276
01:40:11.158 --> 01:40:13.786
But I got a plane. 
I'll be there.

1277
01:40:13.911 --> 01:40:16.622
Every time I turn around,
somebody gets to him.


1278
01:40:16.747 --> 01:40:20.543
Now they're talking about postponing.

1279
01:40:24.588 --> 01:40:29.218
- Cleared for Washington?
- Yes, sir. We are.


1280
01:40:32.763 --> 01:40:36.225
"Truman, Stimson arrive Potsdam
for conference with Stalin.


1281
01:40:36.350 --> 01:40:38.644
Advise results of Trinity Test soonest."

1282
01:40:38.769 --> 01:40:41.397
Stalin's gonna eat Truman alive
at this meeting.


1283
01:40:41.522 --> 01:40:44.191
- Unless we...
- Yes, unless...


1284
01:40:44.317 --> 01:40:47.987
we give the president something
lethal to stick in his back pocket.


1285
01:40:48.112 --> 01:40:53.117
I'll tell you something
it won't be... postponement.


1286
01:40:59.040 --> 01:41:03.961
Oh, lord... so close.

1287
01:41:06.047 --> 01:41:08.507
Sir.

1288
01:41:52.385 --> 01:41:57.139
Keep going down slow.

1289
01:41:59.725 --> 01:42:03.020
His heart looks larger. Could be
fluid in the pericardial sac.


1290
01:42:03.145 --> 01:42:04.897
- Radiation induced?
- Probably.


1291
01:42:05.022 --> 01:42:07.358
It's almost doubled in size overnight.

1292
01:42:07.483 --> 01:42:10.027
If this continues, his heart will drown.

1293
01:42:10.152 --> 01:42:12.571
- Is he lucid?
- In and out.


1294
01:42:12.697 --> 01:42:16.450
There's tremendous brain swelling
from the radiation.


1295
01:42:16.575 --> 01:42:21.205
- What happens next?
- I don't know. I mean, I have no idea.


1296
01:42:21.330 --> 01:42:24.750
No human being's ever gotten
this dose of radiation before.


1297
01:42:24.875 --> 01:42:26.711
He's dying from the inside out.

1298
01:42:26.836 --> 01:42:31.465
Other problems. His gastrointestinal
tract has been destroyed by radiation.


1299
01:42:31.590 --> 01:42:34.677
Excuse me, doctors.

1300
01:42:39.515 --> 01:42:42.643
You've got to believe
we're doing everything we know how.


1301
01:42:42.768 --> 01:42:44.228
Absolutely everything.

1302
01:42:44.353 --> 01:42:48.065
It's not gonna do any good
to have you ripping yourself apart.


1303
01:42:48.190 --> 01:42:52.695
- You've got to go home and sleep.
- Richard, I can't.


1304
01:43:50.961 --> 01:43:52.421
- Some orange.
- Sure is.


1305
01:43:52.546 --> 01:43:54.840
Hey, Oppie?

1306
01:44:07.937 --> 01:44:10.231
Look out!

1307
01:44:11.732 --> 01:44:13.442
Hornig?

1308
01:44:13.567 --> 01:44:15.861
- Hornig?
- It's all right.


1309
01:44:15.987 --> 01:44:18.739
The other safety's holding.

1310
01:44:20.741 --> 01:44:24.453
Does anybody else need a martini?

1311
01:44:26.497 --> 01:44:29.291
- What's the word?
- Oppie, it doesn't look good.


1312
01:44:29.417 --> 01:44:35.172
We have a chance of thunderstorms
over the next five days. I'm sorry.


1313
01:44:35.923 --> 01:44:39.635
I'm not telling you
what this guy's got up there.


1314
01:44:59.155 --> 01:45:01.157
- Why wasn't I told?
- Too much panic.


1315
01:45:01.282 --> 01:45:03.326
- How is he?
- Difficult to tell.


1316
01:45:03.451 --> 01:45:05.953
- I'd like to see him.
- We're not permitting visits.


1317
01:45:06.078 --> 01:45:08.748
But the men who were
with him have been spoken to.


1318
01:45:08.873 --> 01:45:11.208
Security. Delicate time.

1319
01:45:11.334 --> 01:45:15.296
He's a strong young man.
He'll pull through.


1320
01:45:15.713 --> 01:45:18.090
Schoenfield, how is he?

1321
01:45:18.215 --> 01:45:21.344
- Is he conscious?
- He's in and out.


1322
01:45:21.469 --> 01:45:23.888
He wants to know
if you read the petition.


1323
01:45:24.013 --> 01:45:28.100
- It means a lot to him.
- Yes, I have.


1324
01:45:28.225 --> 01:45:31.270
And then, that's it? That's all?

1325
01:45:31.395 --> 01:45:34.315
Yes, I have and then now
I wash my hands of it?


1326
01:45:34.440 --> 01:45:36.150
Now wait a minute, Oppenheimer.

1327
01:45:36.275 --> 01:45:39.278
I got a friend falling apart
who thinks you got the answers.


1328
01:45:39.403 --> 01:45:41.072
That's what you let him think.

1329
01:45:41.197 --> 01:45:45.451
Do you know what the Christ is going on,
or is the whole thing out of control?


1330
01:45:45.576 --> 01:45:47.995
If you're trying to make a point,
what is it?


1331
01:45:48.120 --> 01:45:51.207
I have spent the last
two years of my life


1332
01:45:51.332 --> 01:45:55.878
putting up with all your security
and your secrecy and your control.


1333
01:45:56.003 --> 01:45:59.048
I don't think that bullshit
was to keep what was going on


1334
01:45:59.173 --> 01:46:02.009
from the Germans
or the Japanese or the Russians.


1335
01:46:02.134 --> 01:46:04.553
It's to keep it from
American Jacks and Jills


1336
01:46:04.679 --> 01:46:06.972
because they may not
like what's going on.


1337
01:46:07.098 --> 01:46:10.017
American people don't
want to know what's going on.


1338
01:46:10.142 --> 01:46:12.603
They want to know
that their sons are alive.


1339
01:46:12.728 --> 01:46:15.856
I'm doing everything in my power
to see that they do.


1340
01:46:15.982 --> 01:46:18.693
Like Oak Ridge, where they're
injecting ill and old


1341
01:46:18.818 --> 01:46:21.195
people with huge doses of plutonium?

1342
01:46:21.320 --> 01:46:24.115
I don't know about Oak Ridge,
but if you want to ask


1343
01:46:24.240 --> 01:46:27.618
what's happening, ask this:
Will it be big enough?


1344
01:46:27.743 --> 01:46:31.080
Big enough to scare all of us
and make us stop and think?


1345
01:46:31.205 --> 01:46:35.292
Big enough to stop all war forever?
You want to ask a question, ask that.


1346
01:46:35.418 --> 01:46:38.754
Look, I've seen Oak Ridge, all right?

1347
01:46:38.879 --> 01:46:41.966
That place wasn't built
to make one or two bombs.


1348
01:46:42.091 --> 01:46:45.511
It was built to make
thousands of them. Thousands.


1349
01:46:45.636 --> 01:46:48.389
And soon everybody's
gonna have a bomb. They will.


1350
01:46:48.514 --> 01:46:52.393
What do they do with them?
Sit and wait till they go off, until "boom"?


1351
01:46:52.518 --> 01:46:55.187
Then we got one world
full of Michael Merrimans


1352
01:46:55.312 --> 01:46:58.733
dying from the inside out.
Is that what you're looking for?


1353
01:46:58.858 --> 01:47:03.112
Because that's the future
you've made for us.


1354
01:47:03.237 --> 01:47:07.450
Hey, Oppenheimer! Oppenheimer,
you ought to stop playing god


1355
01:47:07.575 --> 01:47:12.872
because you are not good at it
and the position is taken.


1356
01:47:23.466 --> 01:47:28.554
His pressure's falling fast.
You've got to get that fluid out now.


1357
01:47:32.350 --> 01:47:35.102
Needle, Michael.

1358
01:47:35.227 --> 01:47:38.189
OK, you're in. 
Start to pull it back.

1359
01:47:38.314 --> 01:47:41.108
Hang in, Michael.

1360
01:47:42.360 --> 01:47:45.112
Hang in, pal.

1361
01:47:45.529 --> 01:47:48.616
Come on, doc.

1362
01:47:49.283 --> 01:47:53.537
Pressure's starting to rise.
It's coming up slowly.


1363
01:48:12.682 --> 01:48:16.769
- Robert, you have to get some sleep.
- God.


1364
01:48:16.894 --> 01:48:20.314
I'm in a dark place.

1365
01:48:20.648 --> 01:48:23.567
We've all cooked this stew.

1366
01:48:23.693 --> 01:48:31.325
The Germans and the Japanese
and the Americans and the Brits.


1367
01:48:31.450 --> 01:48:35.746
It's an ugliness that goes back.
It goes way back.


1368
01:48:35.871 --> 01:48:39.625
I'm not a scientist anymore.

1369
01:48:39.750 --> 01:48:44.672
I'm a goddamn functionary.

1370
01:48:45.089 --> 01:48:48.009
I've got to stay in control.

1371
01:48:48.134 --> 01:48:51.804
I've got to control who gets this thing.

1372
01:48:51.929 --> 01:48:56.934
Power and control,
it's all I ever hear about anymore.


1373
01:48:57.143 --> 01:48:59.687
Doesn't life matter to you?

1374
01:48:59.812 --> 01:49:02.398
What about love and understanding?

1375
01:49:02.523 --> 01:49:06.110
I thought that's what science
was all about.


1376
01:49:06.235 --> 01:49:09.280
I just wanted us to work.

1377
01:49:09.405 --> 01:49:15.161
Does everything have to be
sacrificed to this... thing?


1378
01:49:16.495 --> 01:49:19.874
I put up with...

1379
01:49:22.376 --> 01:49:24.795
Jean,

1380
01:49:24.920 --> 01:49:28.966
because I thought you needed her.

1381
01:49:30.176 --> 01:49:33.471
And I thought you'd give
her up because of me.


1382
01:49:34.388 --> 01:49:37.308
But she didn't count.

1383
01:49:37.433 --> 01:49:44.815
I don't count. Nothing counts for you
anymore except this damn bomb.


1384
01:49:44.940 --> 01:49:47.443
That's what it is.

1385
01:49:47.568 --> 01:49:50.905
But it's not your only creation.

1386
01:49:51.030 --> 01:49:54.492
There are the children.

1387
01:49:55.117 --> 01:50:00.748
And you need my love and support.
I know.


1388
01:50:00.873 --> 01:50:03.000
I don't...

1389
01:50:03.125 --> 01:50:06.295
I don't know where it is.

1390
01:50:06.420 --> 01:50:09.548
Why me?

1391
01:50:11.133 --> 01:50:14.428
Why did he pick me?

1392
01:50:36.701 --> 01:50:38.786
- Panton!
- Sir?


1393
01:50:38.911 --> 01:50:42.707
Security's a mess. Nobody at
the checkpoint. Nobody up here.


1394
01:50:42.832 --> 01:50:45.710
- What do you think this is, a beach?
- No, sir.


1395
01:50:45.835 --> 01:50:48.796
We've got to call a halt.
The weather is unpredictable.


1396
01:50:48.921 --> 01:50:51.507
We are not calling a halt
on account of weather.


1397
01:50:51.632 --> 01:50:55.386
With the wind we could send
radioactive junk all the way to Amarillo.


1398
01:50:55.511 --> 01:50:59.306
You The New York Times reporter?
I want three reports.


1399
01:50:59.432 --> 01:51:02.727
One if we succeed, one if we fail
and one if we disintegrate.


1400
01:51:02.852 --> 01:51:06.731
With the wind blowing this direction,
Amarillo could get a fallout.


1401
01:51:06.856 --> 01:51:09.358
- Fermi's right.
- No, I'm saying no.


1402
01:51:09.483 --> 01:51:12.862
The decision is mine!

1403
01:51:12.987 --> 01:51:15.031
- Do you understand?
- We can't do it.


1404
01:51:15.156 --> 01:51:18.534
We go ahead with this. Sergeant,
do something about that dog.


1405
01:51:18.659 --> 01:51:21.329
You sound like you're planning
a railway schedule.


1406
01:51:21.454 --> 01:51:25.249
No, you are trying to uninvent this.

1407
01:51:25.374 --> 01:51:26.876
I can do it without you.

